I was talking to a friend this morning about my inner peace about my breakup, I realized I’m in this weird space of rediscovering myself and choosing to blossom freely and fully. I remember conditioning myself to think love was only a forever deal and happiness was a home & a husband. When that was ripped from me I literally thought life itself was over. I am in the process of understanding we all have more than one soulmate, love isn’t always till death do you part, and happiness is a journey not a destination. I learned there are 3 kinds of people who love: the first is a person who’s palm is out and a butterfly lands. They are so excited to love that they curl their palm tightly crushing or jailing the butterfly. The second person shoos the butterfly away for fear of becoming attached to it. And the third person lets the butterfly land and uses their other hand to shield the wind, but lets it leave when it desires. Let love live for as long or as little as it wants, don’t cage anyone or let yourself get caged. Because in the end you can say you are one of the few who knows what Love feels like. 🦋

I left home at 18yrs old. Not because I had to but because I was ashamed at the "path" I chose. My Mom literally did everything by herself and made that shit look easy & graceful. Every single thing I do, she is always in mind. Every single success I have is because she's in my corner. Every single failure I have is 100% because I didn't listen to her. God knows I don't deserve her and he reminds me every single day that I am blessed and need to show gratitude, love, and thankfulness to my Mother. Even if she does FaceTime me and just watch the news. Or ask me "what do I always say" (when she "always says" everything). Or when she leaves me 18 vmails tell me "it's your mother didn't really want anything". Or when she tells me something I already know and I scream at her "I'm not 5"....like a 5 yr old would do! I love you more than all the blue in the ocean and sky combined💗 Happy Mothers Day @taralafex 😘

This started with gymnastics and she trickled it into everything in life. “Mom I’m nervous about my presentation”.....”meditate before you go into that class” “Mom I’m heading into warmups now”.....”make sure you meditate before you go out there”. This picture was not posed contrary to what it looks like. I caught my Mom doing her very own meditation before she got out of bed and I happened to be drinking out of my Buddha cup💫Thank you universe for your small signs of beauty like my Momma🕉🧘🏽‍♀️✨

I woke up feeling like I never truly fell asleep. Mike really wasn’t my “step dad” because I was too old for that when my Mom chose him, but he was in my life. I knew going home from college I was going home to my Mom and him. He would tell any stranger who would listen that I was a national champ and I was the best gymnast in the world. “Big Show” he called me. He would completely ignore my Mom’s request to put onions in the eggs because he knew I hate onions. No ones perfect and everyone sins different. My Mom is the greatest human to walk this planet and I just feel for her right now in an all around way because I know what being a strong person is like. You take all the worlds problems on and you do yours last. Mike was the best version of himself with my Mom, she has this weird ability in making the people around her great. Rest easy Mike🥀
